Column properties:
This columns CSS shorthand property sets the number of columns to use when drawing an element's contents, as well as those columns' widths.


column-count    	    this specifies the number of columns an element should be divided into
column-gap	          this specifies the gap between the columns
column-rule	          this shorthand property for setting all the column-rule-* properties
column-rule-color	    this specifies the color of the rule between columns
column-rule-style	    this specifies the style of the rule between columns
column-rule-width	    this specifies how many columns an element should span across
column-span           this specifies a seperate block width for the element moving down the column contents seperately



----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Example:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<title>Online CSS Editor</title>
<head>
<style>
div{
    border:5px solid red;
    column-count:3;
    column-width:100px;
    column-gap:50px;
    column-rule: 2px dotted blue;
}
h1{
    column-span:all;
    text-align:center;
}
p{
    padding:10px;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div>
    <h1>Column CSS</h1>
